issue.title: Column header positioning is inconsistent while dragging the header to reorder its position in the table
issue.body:
### Version Information
v2.20.1
### Environment
Development

### What is the expected behaviour?
When we try to drag the column header to re-order the headers, it should positioned correctly, that is from the source that needs to be re-ordered.

### What is the current behaviour?
When we try to drag a particular header to re-order its position, the header is not positioned consistently.

### How to reproduce the issue?

1. Drag a table in the canvas
2. Select any column header that needs to be re-ordered and drag it, you can observe, its starting point is inconsistent.

### Screenshots or Screencast
[My app 1697187833826 - ToolJet - 13 October 2023 - Watch Video](https://www.loom.com/share/f276334d5e224ec38834d6fb409289be)

### If the bug is confirmed, would you be willing to submit a PR?
Yes

issue.title: Error page when an app link is unreachable
issue.body: User Story: "As a user, I want to be informed and guided when I cannot access an app due to network errors or server-related issues, so I can take appropriate actions." Acceptance Criteria: 1. When the app URL is not reachable due to network errors or server-related issues, the system should display an error page with the following content: - Title:Oops, something went wrong! - Helper Text: An error occurred while loading the app. Please try again or contact the admin. 2. The error page should provide two Call-to-Action (CTA) buttons: - A CTA to allow the user to reload the page. - A CTA to enable the user to return to the home page or dashboard. By implementing this, the user will have a clear understanding of the issue and the necessary actions to take when facing connectivity problems with the app. Deisgn -
